# Enum.reduce over a Range receiver dispatches Enumerable to the Range impl (a
# different target type than List). Expected: int.
#
# Target status: pinned in type_infer. The engine models Range as the existing
# opaque impl-target receiver with field-wise struct proof for `first`, `last`,
# and `step`. Protocol devirtualization then chooses Enumerable.Range.reduce/3,
# and struct-field projection feeds the callback enough type information for
# public Enum.reduce/3 to settle to int.
fn main() do
  dbg(Enum.reduce(1..3, 0, fn (x, a) -> x + a end))
end
